# Return True if all columns have the same sums?def tstCol(sum: int, t: list) -> bool:?    n = len(t[0])?    isMagic = True?    for row in range(0, n):?        colSum = 0?        for col in range(0, n):?            colSum = colSum + t[col][row]?        if colSum != sum:?            isMagic = False?    return isMagic?# Return True if all rows have the same sums?def tstRows(sum: int, t: list) -> bool:?    n = len(t[0])?    isMagic = True?    for col in range(0, n):?        rowSum = 0?        for row in range(0, n):?            rowSum = rowSum + t[col][row]?        if rowSum != sum:?            isMagic = False?    return isMagic?# Return True if the two diagonal have the same sums?def tstDiag(sum: int, t: list) -> bool:?    n = len(t[0])?    sumDiag0 = 0?    sumDiag1 = 0?    for i in range(0, n):?        sumDiag0 = sumDiag0 + t[i][i]?        sumDiag1 = sumDiag1 + t[n - i - 1][n - i - 1]?    return sumDiag0 == sumDiag1 == sum?# Return True if the table is a magic square?def carre_magique(t: list) -> bool:?    sum = 0?    for i in range(0, len(t[0])):?        sum = sum + t[0][i]?    return tstCol(sum, t) and tstRows(sum, t) and tstDiag(sum, t)?# Return True if the table is a perfect magic square?def carre_magique_parfait(t: list) -> bool:?    if carre_magique(t):?        n = len(t[0])?        carList = []?        isMagic = True?        for i in range(0, n ** 2):?            carList.append(i + 1)?        for row in range(0, n):?            for col in range(0, n):?                nb = t[row][col]?                if carList.__contains__(nb):?                    carList.remove(nb)?                else:?                    isMagic = False?        return isMagic?    else:?        return False
